Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba tweeted that a friend of his was killed by Zuma&#8217;s blue light brigade. CAPE TOWN - The South African Police Service (SAPS) has dismissed allegations that a convoy accompanying President Jacob Zuma was involved in a pedestrian accident.City of Johannesburg Mayor Herman Mashaba tweeted that a friend of his was killed by Zuma s blue light brigade.The SAPS has confirmed that a 59-year-old man was hit by a vehicle apparently driven by a member of Zuma s presidential protection unit. He subsequently died from his injuries. Police says the driver of the vehicle was on duty at the time of the incident and a case of culpable homicide has been opened.SAPS spokesperson Brigadier Mashadi Selepe says the incident did not occur while President Zuma was in transit but happened in the Pretoria CBD. The driver of the police vehicle is a member of the presidential protection unit in the SAPS and at the time of the incident the member was on duty. But we also need to clarify that there was no convoy at the time of the incident. The Presidency says Zuma was attending the National Council of Provinces Taking Parliament to the People engagement in East London at the time of the incident.Mashaba says he is aware the president himself was not part of the convoy.